Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Custom Allocators Module

Provides advanced custom memory allocation strategies for high-performance and specialized use cases.

Features:
- Arena, pool, slab, stack, region, and hybrid allocators
- Pluggable allocator interface
- Allocation/deallocation hooks
- Alignment, zeroing, and guard support
- Memory tracking, leak detection, and debugging
- Thread-local and global allocators
- NUMA-aware allocation
- Error handling and fallback strategies
- AI/agent-friendly allocation APIs
- Production-ready, robust, and extensible
:End Note

Note: Allocator Types and Interfaces
Type Allocator is Dictionary with:
    name as String
    allocate as Function that takes size as Integer and alignment as Integer returns Pointer
    deallocate as Function that takes pointer as Pointer and size as Integer and alignment as Integer
    reset as Optional[Function that takes no arguments returns None]
    stats as AllocatorStats
    config as AllocatorConfig
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type AllocatorStats is Dictionary with:
    total_allocated as Integer
    total_freed as Integer
    current_usage as Integer
    peak_usage as Integer
    allocation_count as Integer
    deallocation_count as Integer
    error_count as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type AllocatorConfig is Dictionary with:
    alignment as Integer
    zero_memory as Boolean
    guard_pages as Boolean
    thread_local as Boolean
    numa_node as Optional[Integer]
    fallback_allocator as Optional[Allocator]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type Pointer is Dictionary with:
    address as Integer
    size as Integer
    alignment as Integer
    allocator as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core Allocator Implementations
Process called "create_arena_allocator" that takes config as AllocatorConfig returns Allocator:
    Note: Arena allocator implementation
    Return Allocator with:
        name as "arena"
        allocate as arena_allocate
        deallocate as arena_deallocate
        reset as arena_reset
        stats as AllocatorStats with:
            total_allocated as 0
            total_freed as 0
            current_usage as 0
            peak_usage as 0
            allocation_count as 0
            deallocation_count as 0
            error_count as 0
            metadata as dictionary containing
        config as config
        metadata as dictionary containing

